13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 82 O.S. 2021, Section 1020.19, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 1020.19. Upon request of a majority of the landowners
17 residing within a basin or subbasin, the Board is authorized to
18 require that water wells be metered and that such meters as the
19 Board shall approve be utilized by the applicant and placed under
20 seal, subject to reading by the agents of the Board at any time.
21 The Board may also require that the applicant report the reading of
22 such meters at reasonable intervals
23 A. The Oklahoma Water Resources Board shall require all permit
24 holders authorized to take and use groundwater to implement a system
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1807 Page 1

1 of m easuring groundwater usage from all wells associated with the
2 permit. The Board shall determine which measurement systems may be
3 utilized, which shall include, but not be limited to, pump and
4 irrigation monitoring telemetry devices capable of reporting usage.
5 Such measuring systems shall be in proper operating conditions at
6 all times when groundwater is being produced. Data from the
7 measuring system shall be utilized for the annual groundwater use
8 report.
9 B. To encourage groundwater conservation, beginning January 1,
10 2026, the Board shall provide a five-year flex allocation of
11 groundwater usage based off the previously determined allocated
12 annual use of the basin or subbasin. A five-year flex allocation
13 shall not require a new permit for existing permit holders. A five-
14 year flex allocation shall be available for:
15 1. Existing permit holders for groundwater use permits in
16 basins or subbasins, based upon the maximum annual yield
17 determination at the time of the original application;
18 2. New applicants for groundwater use permits in basins or
19 subbasins based upon the current maximum annual yield determination;
20 and
21 3. New and existing applicants and temporary permit holders for
22 groundwater use permits in basins or subbasins where the maximum
23 annual yield has yet to be determined.
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1807 Page 2

1 C. An applicant for a five-year flex allocation shall be
2 required to:
3 1. Submit an annual usage report of the prior year's usage from
4 a Board-approved water measurement system; and
5 2. Pay the annual groundwater permit fee.
6 D. A five-year flex allocation shall allow the permit holder to
7 exceed the determined annual allocation in any year of the five-year
8 allocation; provided, that the applicant shall adhere to the
9 cumulative annually determined allocation of the basin or subbasin
10 over the five-year period. The permit holder shall not exceed the
11 permitted annual allocation by over two hundred percent (200%) in
12 any of the five (5) years.
13 E. Nothing in this section shall apply to domestic wells.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
15 Passed the House of Representatives the 12th day of March, 2025.
